    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-06-10T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-06-10T01:00:00-05:00" n="1115"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1115">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.5293/6–1047: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-06-10T15:00:00+09:00"
                            >June 10, 1947—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 10—3:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1400. Shanghai Bureau of Land Administration has not yet replied to Consulate
                    General’s request for general extension of time limit for registration on behalf
                    unknown American landowners (mytel 800, May 8, repeated Department as 1123, May
                    8, 7 p.m. and my despatch to Department No. 1205, May 13<note n="22"
                        xml:id="d1115fn1">Latter not printed.</note>). Land Bureau apparently has
                    adopted practice of granting extension of 1 month in cases where Consulate
                    General has notified it of names of individuals who were unable comply with
                    original time limit. In reply to such notifications Land Bureau sends
                    mimeographed letter pertinent part of which reads “since the said owner has
                    factual difficulty permission is hereby granted to reserve the time limit for
                    application for 1 month from the <pb facs="1406" n="1396" xml:id="pg_1396"/>
                    date of receipt of this letter.” In most cases this gives owners until mid-July
                    to register. Consulate General will, if necessary, request further extensions
                    for those who are unable to comply within this extended period of 1 month.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
